 TV series)|Vikings]]''\n|}\n{{col-float-end}}\n\n==Special awards==\nSeveral special awards were given:<ref>[http://membership.academy.ca/Canadian-Screen-Awards/2015-Nominees-Winners/Special-Awards 2015 Academy Special Awards] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170317055117/http://membership.academy.ca/Canadian-Screen-Awards/2015-Nominees-Winners/Special-Awards |date=2017-03-17 }}. ''[[Academy of Canadian Cinema & Television]]'', March 2015.</ref>\n*Board of Directors' Tribute: [[George Anthony (journalist)|George Anthony]]\n*Digital Media Trailblazing Award: Jeffrey Elliott\n*[[Earle Grey Award]]: [[Paul Gross]]\n*Fan Choice Award: [[Anna Silk]]\n*[[Gordon Sinclair Award]]: [[Ric Esther Bienstock]]\n*Humanitarian Award: [[Michael Landsberg]]\n*Icon Award: Insight Productions\n*Legacy Award: [[Toronto International Film Festival]]\n*[[Margaret Collier Award]]: [[Tassie Cameron]]\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*[http://www.academy.ca/awards/ Canadian Screen Awards]\n\n{{Canadian Screen Awards}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Canadian Screen Awards, 03}}\n[[Category:Canadian Screen Awards|03]]\n[[Category:2015 in Canadian cinema]]\n[[Category:2014 film awards]]\n[[Category:2014 television awards]]\n[[Category:2015 in Toronto]]\n[[Category:2015 in Canadian television]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|3rd year of awards given by the Academy of Canadian Cinema & Television}}\n{{Infobox award\n| name = 3rd Canadian Screen Awards\n| image =\n| date = March 1, 2015\n| location =  [[Four Seasons Centre for the Performing Arts]], Toronto\n| host = [[Andrea Martin]]\n| most_awards = Film: ''[[Mommy (2014 film)|Mommy]]'' (9)  <br /> TV: ''[[Orphan Black]]'' (10)\n| most_nominations = Film: ''Mommy'' (13) <br /> TV: ''Orphan Black'' (13)\n| award1_type = Best Motion Picture\n| award1_winner = ''Mommy''\n| award2_type = Best Dramatic Series\n| award2_winner = ''Orphan Black ''\n| award3_type = Best Comedy Series\n| award3_winner = ''[[Call Me Fitz]]''\n| network = [[CBC Television|CBC]]\n| previous = [[2nd Canadian Screen Awards|2nd]]\n| main = [[Canadian Screen Awards]]\n| next =[[4th Canadian Screen Awards|4th]]\n}}\nThe '''3rd [[Canadian Screen Awards]]''' were held on March 1, 2015, to honour achievements in [[Canada|Canadian]] film, television and digital media production in 2014.<ref name=nominations>[http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/canadian-screen-awards-unveil-nominations-763287 \"Canadian Screen Awards Unveil Nominations\"]. [[The Hollywood Reporter]], January 13, 2015.</ref>\n\nNominations were announced on January 13, 2015.<ref name=nominations /> On the film side, ''[[Mommy (2014 film)|Mommy]]'' led with 13 nominations, while on the television side the science fiction series ''[[Orphan Black]]'' also received 13 nominations.\n\nThe awards ceremony were hosted by [[Andrea Martin]] at the [[Four Seasons Centre for the Performing Arts]] in Toronto, Ontario. Awards in many of the technical categories were presented in a series of galas over the week before the main ceremony.\n\nChanges to the awards over previous years included the introduction of new categories for [[Canadian Screen Award for Best Cinematography in a Documentary|Best Cinematography in a Documentary]] and [[Canadian Screen Award for Best Editing in a Documentary|Best Editing in a Documentary]].\n\n==Film==\n{| class=wikitable\n|-\n! style=\"background:#EEDD82; width:50%\" | [[Canadian Screen Award for Best Motion Picture|Motion Picture]]\n! style=\"background:#EEDD82; width:50%\" | [[Canadian Screen Award for Best Director|Direction]]\n|-\n| valign=\"top\" |\n*{{blue ribbon}} '''''[[Mommy (2014 film)|Mommy]]'' \u2014 [[Xavier Dolan]], [[Nancy Grant]]'''\n*''[[Cast No Shadow (film)|Cast No Shadow]]'' \u2014 [[Chris Agoston]], [[Christian Sparkes]], [[Allison White (producer)|Allison White]]\n*''[[Fall (2014 film)|Fall]]'' \u2014 [[Mehernaz Lentin]]\n*''[[In Her Place]]'' \u2014 [[Albert Shin]], [[Igor Drljaca]], [[Yoon Hyun Chan]]\n*'